20 years younger.

847
00:57:51,555 --> 00:57:54,993
I've made you feel
20 years younger.

848
00:57:55,123 --> 00:57:58,736
Harry, you owe me.

849
00:58:26,024 --> 00:58:27,895
Don't you think
you've had enough?

850
00:58:28,026 --> 00:58:31,551
Vodka with a twist.
Double.

851
00:58:31,682 --> 00:58:33,292
Excuse me.

852
00:58:33,422 --> 00:58:35,337
Mr. Helmsley?

853
00:58:35,468 --> 00:58:37,426
I'm Deborah pauley,

854
00:58:37,557 --> 00:58:39,341
and I know this
is terribly gauche,

855
00:58:39,472 --> 00:58:41,387
but I saw you
and Mrs. Helmsley

856
00:58:41,518 --> 00:58:43,128
on the dance floor
a while ago

857
00:58:43,258 --> 00:58:46,392
and well, my husband
would kill me,

858
00:58:46,523 --> 00:58:47,915
but he's not
a very good dancer,

859
00:58:48,046 --> 00:58:51,353
<i>and i--</i><i>
I love the samba.</i>

860
00:58:51,484 --> 00:58:54,487
Mrs. Helmsley,
would you mind
very much

861
00:58:54,618 --> 00:58:55,662
if I asked
your husband
to dance?

862
00:58:57,969 --> 00:59:00,537
There's not a chance
in hell that's gonna
happen, honey.

863
00:59:13,114 --> 00:59:15,943
Harry: <i>
That young lady was</i><i>
so charming and so innocent.</i>

864
00:59:16,074 --> 00:59:18,555
Leona: <i>Innocent?!</i><i>
You are more innocent</i><i>
than she is.</i>

865
00:59:18,685 --> 00:59:21,558
Harry: Oh yeah?
Well, let me ask
you something.

866
00:59:21,688 --> 00:59:25,083
Damn it to hell!
Don't keep walking
away from me.

867
00:59:25,213 --> 00:59:26,867
- I am trying
to talk to you!
- If I am so vulgar,

868
00:59:26,998 --> 00:59:29,130
why don't you crawl
back to your sweet,
simple Eve?

869
00:59:29,261 --> 00:59:30,784
Don't think that
hasn't crossed my mind.

870
00:59:30,915 --> 00:59:33,526
At least I had
some peace then.

871
00:59:33,657 --> 00:59:35,484
I could fight my battles
in the office,

872
00:59:35,615 --> 00:59:37,269
but home was like
a sanctuary--

873
00:59:37,399 --> 00:59:39,967
- calm and peaceful.
- <i>It was killing you.</i>

874
00:59:40,098 --> 00:59:42,056
You were becoming
an old man.

875
00:59:42,187 --> 00:59:44,972
Sometimes
you suffocate me.

876
00:59:45,103 --> 00:59:48,062
<i>In public,</i><i>
you grab ahold of me</i><i>
like a jealous schoolgirl.</i>

877
00:59:48,193 --> 00:59:50,412
You comb my hair,
pick the lint off
my jacket.

878
00:59:50,543 --> 00:59:52,632
You treat me like--

879
00:59:52,763 --> 00:59:56,723
I treat you like
you are the center
of my universe.

880
00:59:56,854 --> 00:59:58,943
[ Groans ]

881
00:59:59,073 --> 01:00:01,249
When I'm with you,
it's--

882
01:00:03,600 --> 01:00:06,907
it's as if
everything else
is out of focus.

883
01:00:07,038 --> 01:00:09,475
You're right.

884
01:00:09,606 --> 01:00:12,521
I don't want
anybody else near you.

885
01:00:12,652 --> 01:00:14,915
And I would be
perfectly willing

886
01:00:15,046 --> 01:00:18,397
to kill anybody
who tried to take
you away from me.

887
01:00:18,527 --> 01:00:21,835
Harry.

888
01:00:21,966 --> 01:00:25,622
Harry!

889
01:00:28,625 --> 01:00:30,627
If anything
happened to you,

890
01:00:33,542 --> 01:00:36,981
I would die.

891
01:00:37,111 --> 01:00:39,897
Together,
we're immortal.

892
01:00:42,900 --> 01:00:45,685
We make magic.

893
01:00:48,601 --> 01:00:52,431
Everything I do

894
01:00:52,561 --> 01:00:56,043
I do for you.

895
01:00:56,174 --> 01:00:59,525
So you better
decide, Harry--

896
01:00:59,656 --> 01:01:02,659
what is it
you really want?

897
01:01:05,139 --> 01:01:08,316
Sweet, simple Eve

898
01:01:10,057 --> 01:01:13,408
or me?

899
01:01:40,740 --> 01:01:42,524
Ladies and gentlemen,
I'm sure you're all wondering

900
01:01:42,655 --> 01:01:44,657
why I called
you here today.

901
01:01:44,788 --> 01:01:48,095
Well, it's for
a very special reason--

902
01:01:48,226 --> 01:01:51,533
the unveiling
of our plans

903
01:01:51,664 --> 01:01:53,927
to build the most
magnificent hotel

904
01:01:54,058 --> 01:01:56,930
New York
has yet to see.

905
01:01:57,061 --> 01:02:00,368
I give you
the palace hotel.

906
01:02:06,723 --> 01:02:10,117
As this model
clearly shows,

907
01:02:10,248 --> 01:02:12,424
we've kept our promise.
We've done everything
possible

908
01:02:12,554 --> 01:02:15,949
<i>to preserve and restore</i><i>
this exquisite villa</i>

909
01:02:16,080 --> 01:02:19,039
<i>by connecting it</i><i>
to the tower behind.</i>

910
01:02:19,170 --> 01:02:22,129
<i>The palace will be</i><i>
the finest hotel</i><i>
in New York.</i>

911
01:02:22,260 --> 01:02:24,697
<i>No expense</i><i>
will be spared.</i>

912
01:02:24,828 --> 01:02:26,960
Now I want to introduce
you to the woman

913
01:02:27,091 --> 01:02:29,180
who will
not only oversee

914
01:02:29,310 --> 01:02:31,225
the creation
of this magnificent hotel,

915
01:02:31,356 --> 01:02:34,620
<i>but will also be president</i><i>
of the newly-formed</i>

916
01:02:34,751 --> 01:02:37,188
Harley hotels
across the country--

917
01:02:37,318 --> 01:02:39,190
Leona Helmsley.

918
01:02:39,320 --> 01:02:42,410
<i>[ Applause ]</i>

919
01:02:51,855 --> 01:02:54,205
I want to know
what we can throw out,

920
01:02:54,335 --> 01:02:56,773
what we can keep.

921
01:02:56,903 --> 01:02:59,384
Okay, what you wanna do
is preserve the interior

922
01:02:59,514 --> 01:03:00,994
to the fullest
possible extent

923
01:03:01,125 --> 01:03:02,343
because of
the historic nature.

924
01:03:02,474 --> 01:03:05,085
The cubicles
the church put in--
they can go.

925
01:03:05,216 --> 01:03:07,000
- Mark, are you
taking notes?
- Yes, ma'am.

926
01:03:07,131 --> 01:03:09,046
The gold room,
thank god,

927
01:03:09,176 --> 01:03:10,264
is pretty much
the way it was.

928
01:03:10,395 --> 01:03:12,223
And the chandelier's intact.

929
01:03:12,353 --> 01:03:15,356
- <i>But in here--</i><i>
Mrs. Helmsley?</i>
- Huh?

930
01:03:15,487 --> 01:03:19,012
In here, we're talking
millions of dollars.

931
01:03:19,143 --> 01:03:21,014
I know that, Sarah.

932
01:03:21,145 --> 01:03:22,799
I don't care
about that.

933
01:03:26,585 --> 01:03:28,500
The rag.

934
01:03:36,247 --> 01:03:38,771
Now, I have the highest
possible standards.

935
01:03:38,902 --> 01:03:41,252
If we are gonna spend
millions of dollars

936
01:03:41,382 --> 01:03:44,646
redecorating
and restoring
this hotel,

937
01:03:44,777 --> 01:03:47,127
then I want
only the best
from you.

938
01:03:47,258 --> 01:03:49,086
If you're up to that,
you've got the job.

939
01:03:49,216 --> 01:03:51,958
Oh, I'm up to it,
Mrs. Helmsley.

940
01:03:52,089 --> 01:03:54,091
Good.

941
01:03:54,221 --> 01:03:56,093
Oh, good.

942
01:03:56,223 --> 01:03:58,138
Bring a pad, Mark.
Come on, Sarah.

943
01:04:01,576 --> 01:04:05,015
As you know,
Mrs. Helmsley,

944
01:04:06,190 --> 01:04:07,974
part of the condition
of appointing your son
vice president

945
01:04:08,105 --> 01:04:09,758
of deco incorporated

946
01:04:09,889 --> 01:04:13,893
was that I supervise
all bookkeeping,

947
01:04:14,024 --> 01:04:15,112
- <i>invoices,</i><i>
transactions.</i>
- Yes, Stanley.

948
01:04:17,331 --> 01:04:19,856
Since your son had
little experience
in this field,

949
01:04:19,986 --> 01:04:22,336
Mr. Helmsley felt that
in-house regulations

950
01:04:22,467 --> 01:04:23,947
be put into effect.

951
01:04:24,077 --> 01:04:26,036
Leona: <i>Stanley,</i><i>
are you going to get</i><i>
to the point eventually,</i>

952
01:04:26,166 --> 01:04:27,864
